-- Japanese Sold Net 157.7 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-06-13T23:51:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/japanese-sold-net-157-7-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended June 8 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 157.7 billion yen ($2.0 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 45.4 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 31.9 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 144.2 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 494.2 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 158 billion yen in stocks, and bought 340.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 676.9
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
